What I'm saying is it's rather poor of an idea for Namco to go removing characters to stick with the plot that almost no one is seriously playing the games for. Sure, she was killed, but I don't think too many people would complain "Why is she in this game? She died in the last one!" if it means having a well balanced, fun to play fighting game.
